author: julianfoad
msg: Fix another SVN_EXPERIMENTAL_PRISTINE test failure: update_tests.py 37.
When the update editor adds a file "with history", it was not properly
keeping track of the path to the temporary file holding the copied text.  To
solve this, store each (potential) new text base into the pristine store at
an earlier stage: when storing its details in FB->new_text_base_* or
(window_handler): When completing the text changes, store the resulting
(add_file_with_history): Store the resulting text in the pristine store.
(close_file): Don't install the new text base, as it's already done.
Don't try to delete the copied text base; add a TODO comment about this.
